records.nl_statement: Show that there is no holomorphic function $f$ in the unit disc $D$ that extends continuously to $\partial D$ such that $f(z) = 1/z$ for $z \in \partial D$.
records.lean_header:

open Complex Filter Function Metric Finset
open scoped BigOperators Topology

    (hf : DifferentiableOn ℂ f D) (hfc : ContinuousOn f (closure D)) :
    ¬ ∀ z ∈ (sphere (0 : ℂ) 1), f z = 1 / z :=

  (h₅ : 2 * r > d)
  : Set.Infinite {z : EuclideanSpace ℝ (Fin n) | ‖z - x‖ = r ∧ ‖z - y‖ = r} :=
